>
  <p>ChevyRoots is an independent home for everything Chevrolet. We cover trucks, Corvettes, classics, muscle cars, SUVs, EVs, and the whole community around them — from the factory floor in 1911 to whatever rolled off the line last week.</p>

  <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
  <p>Every other Chevy site on the internet is one of two things: a dealer lead-generation engine dressed up as "content," or a soulless AI-generated spec sheet farm. There wasn't a good place for enthusiasts to get honest, well-written, photo-rich coverage of the trucks and cars they actually drive.</p>

  <p>We built ChevyRoots to be that place. Run by a Chevy girl who actually drives a Silverado ZR2. Written for people who love these vehicles for what they are, not what a salesperson wants them to be.</p>

  <h2>What we publish</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Buyer's guides</strong> — the honest kind. Lease deals, warranty math, dealer negotiation, known issues by year</li>
    <li><strong>Model histories</strong> — generation-by-generation deep dives on every Chevy that matters</li>
    <li><strong>Build features</strong> — community-submitted trucks, restomods, classics, and modern performance builds</li>
    <li><strong>Event coverage</strong> — Crystal attends car shows around the country with photos, video, and full reports</li>
    <li><strong>The known-issues database</strong> — a living reference on common problems by model and year</li>
    <li><strong>The mechanic directory</strong> — shops that actually know what they're doing</li>
    <li><strong>Crystal's Corner</strong> — weekly editorial from the founder herself</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Dealer-paid lead-gen articles disguised as reviews</li>
    <li>Clickbait "Top 10 Shocking Facts" slideshows</li>
    <li>Auto-generated spec sheets ripped from manufacturer press releases</li>
    <li>Inflating every product to five stars for affiliate commissions</li>
    <li>Pretending to be neutral when we have a strong opinion</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we make money</h2>
  <p>ChevyRoots is supported by affiliate commissions from retailers we genuinely recommend (Summit Racing, JEGS, Amazon, etc.), newsletter sponsorships, and — eventually — featured dealer listings and OEM partnerships. Every affiliate link is disclosed. Every sponsored piece is clearly labeled. See the <a href="/disclaimer/">disclaimer page</a> for the full details.</p>

  <h2>Who runs it</h2>
  <p><strong>Crystal</strong> is the founder and editor-in-chief. She drives a Silverado ZR2, has been around Chevys her whole life, and writes Crystal's Corner every week. Her story is on the <a href="/crystal/">meet Crystal</a> page.</p>

  <p>A small editorial team helps with research, fact-checking, and community moderation.</p>

